# ESLint and TypeScript static checks

## What this project uses (not TSLint)

- **TSLint** is deprecated and **not** used. TypeScript style and many type-aware checks come from **ESLint** (**flat config** via root **`eslint.config.mjs`**) with **neostandard**, **typescript-eslint** (v8.x), **eslint-plugin-vue** (v10), and **`@typescript-eslint`**, aligned with **TypeScript ~6.0** in `package.json`.
- **Standalone typecheck**: `yarn lint:typescript` runs **`vue-tsc -p tsconfig.json --noEmit`**, which type-checks **`.vue` SFCs** and all TypeScript in the same project as **`tsc`**. Plain **`tsc`** alone does not load `<script setup>` blocks from SFCs, so it must not be the only check for renderer Vue code. Use `yarn lint:typescript` in CI, before commits, and whenever you change configs or broad typings.
- Use **`import type`** for type-only imports in `.ts` and Vue `<script lang="ts">` blocks; do not keep value imports that are only used as types.
- Prefer explicit type imports over inline `typeof import('...')` type annotations when a named type import can express the same intent.

## Code comments

In line comments, block comments, and JSDoc above APIs and tests: do not use Markdown double-asterisk bold or asterisk italic; use plain wording. For inline references to symbols, paths, or commands, prefer single-quoted text (for example 'yarn test:unit') instead of grave accents (backticks). Do not break sentences mid-clause across ` * ` JSDoc lines for stylistic wrapping; use full lines or a baseline sentence plus ` * - ` bullets (see [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) code comments).

## Commands

| Command | Role |
|--------|------|
| `yarn lint:eslint` | ESLint over `src/`, `src-electron/`, `e2e-tests/`, `types/`, Quasar/Vitest/Playwright configs, and `.storybook-workspace/.storybook/` ‚Äî see `package.json` `lint:eslint` script. |
| `yarn lint:stylelint` | Stylelint on `src/**/*.{vue,css,scss,sass}` and `.storybook-workspace/.storybook/**/*.{vue,css,scss,sass}` (declaration blocks sorted alphabetically via `stylelint-order`; use `yarn lint:stylelint:fix` to autofix). |
| `yarn lint:typescript` | Full **`vue-tsc`** project check (Vue SFCs + `.ts`; Quasar paths via `tsconfig.json` ‚Üí `.quasar/tsconfig.json`). |

## Pre-commit / pre-changelog quality gate

Before commits or changelog edits tied to product or test work, run the four checks **in order** in **one** terminal via **`yarn testbatch:verify`** (see [testing-terminal-isolation.mdc](testing-terminal-isolation.mdc) and [git-conventional-commits.mdc](git-conventional-commits.mdc)).

Run `yarn lint:eslint`, `yarn lint:typescript`, `yarn lint:stylelint`, or `yarn test:unit` individually only while debugging a specific failure.

**Dev server**: `vite-plugin-checker` runs ESLint during `quasar dev`; keep `@typescript-eslint` major in sync with TypeScript so you do not see unsupported-TS-version warnings from `typescript-estree`.

## `tsconfig` and `.vue` / Quasar

- Root **`tsconfig.json`** extends **`.quasar/tsconfig.json`** and excludes the whole **`.quasar`** tree (generated output). **`src/env.d.ts`** declares **`*.vue`** modules and includes **`/// <reference types="vite/client" />`** so **`import.meta.env`** and other Vite typings resolve in the IDE and in **`vue-tsc`** (generated **`.quasar/quasar.d.ts`** also references **`vite/client`**, but **`src/env.d.ts`** keeps SFC scripts consistent when tooling does not load `.quasar` types first).
- Do **not** add a top-level `compilerOptions.paths` override in `tsconfig.json` unless you merge with Quasar‚Äôs `paths`; replacing `paths` breaks `app/`, `src/`, `#q-app/*`, etc.

## `quasar.config.ts` typing notes

- **PWA**: `pwa.workboxMode` must match Quasar types (**`GenerateSW`** | **`InjectManifest`**, PascalCase), not legacy lowercase strings.
- **BEX**: use **`QuasarBexConfiguration`** fields (e.g. `extraScripts`); do not use removed placeholders like `contentScripts` in `bex`.
- **Vite plugins**: the repo may carry a **`@ts-expect-error`** on `defineConfig` when **hoisted `vite`** and **`@quasar/app-vite`‚Äôs nested `vite`** disagree on `Plugin` types; the config is still valid at runtime.

## vue-i18n boot augmentation (`src/boot/i18n.ts`)

- **`declare module 'vue-i18n'`** for `DefineLocaleMessage` / formats can trigger **TS2665** under `tsc` because the package **`module`** entry resolves to an ESM bundle. The boot file uses **`@ts-expect-error`** with a short comment; keep **`eslint-disable @typescript-eslint/no-empty-object-type`** on that augmentation block (rule name in **typescript-eslint v8**).

## Vitest env stubs

- **Vitest 3+**: `vi.stubEnv(name, value)` types **`DEV`**, **`PROD`**, and **`SSR`** as **boolean**; other keys use **`string | undefined`**. Use **`vi.stubEnv('DEV', true)`** / **`false`**, not **`'true'`** / **`''`**, so `tsc` and runtime stubs stay correct.

## Electron / monorepo-style imports in tests

- Prefer **`app/src-electron/...`** (and other **`app/`**-root paths) in Vitest files when the same import must satisfy **`tsc`** and Vitest **`resolve.alias`**, e.g. [`tweaks.vitest.test.ts`](../../src-electron/mainScripts/tests/tweaks.vitest.test.ts).

## Dependency hygiene

- **`npm install --ignore-scripts`** skips **`electron`‚Äôs postinstall** and breaks **`yarn quasar:dev:electron`** until Electron is reinstalled (see [fantasia-dev-setup skill](../skills/fantasia-dev-setup/SKILL.md)).

## Node.js version

- **22.22.0+** required (`package.json` `engines.node`). GitHub Actions builds use **`22.22`** (`.github/workflows/build.yml`). Match locally with `nvm` / `fnm` when debugging CI-only issues.

